v1.30.1 - SECURITY: reject pending-2FA tokens in requireAuth (S-3)

A token issued after a correct password but before the second factor was
accepted by requireAuth as a regular access token. An attacker with a
phished password against a 2FA-enabled account could skip the second
factor AND mint a long-lived API token via /settings/api-tokens,
converting the 5-minute pending window into a persistent takeover.

Fix: verifyAccess now rejects any token carrying a kind claim. Real
access tokens have no kind; pending tokens set kind:'2fa-pending'.
verifyPending is unchanged (the /auth/2fa/login flow still consumes
pending tokens correctly).

Kept the shared access secret + added the verify-time guard rather than
introducing a dedicated JWT_PENDING_SECRET — the guard closes the
vulnerability without forcing operators to rotate .env. Cryptographic
secret separation tracked as a v1.32+ follow-up under phase boundary.

Three regression tests under describe('S-3 regression: ...') in
twoFactor.test.ts: pending token -> 401 on /api/auth/me; pending token
-> 401 on /api/settings/api-tokens (the takeover chain); full happy
path still works.

Verified: tsc clean. twoFactor.test.ts 11/11. Full suite 260 passed,
5 skipped (LDAP), 1 unrelated pre-existing flake (backups.test.ts
BACKUP_DIR env-cache order dependency, passes in isolation).